=== SIGNATURE ===
xmod(a, b)

=== COMMENT ===
One-based modulo: like MOD but cycles 1..b instead of 0..b-1. Equal to MOD(a,b) except when that is 0, where it returns b.

=== CODE ===
=LAMBDA(a, b, IF(MOD(a, b) = 0, b, MOD(a, b)))

=== DESCRIPTION ===
Modulo that returns the divisor instead of zero (1-based).

Arguments:
  a - the dividend.
  b - the divisor.

Returns:
  MOD(a, b), except returns b when MOD(a, b) would be 0. Useful for 1-based cycling.

Example:
  xmod(6, 3)  ->  3
